## DO NOT SKIP
1. Fresh verification record (not cached from previous runs).
2. Evidence-backed claims only (no "should work" or "probably passes").
3. Guardrail domain high-risk checks when applicable.

## Rationalization Red Flags
| Rationalization | Counter-rule |
|---|---|
| "Tests pass so we're done" | Passing tests do not guarantee all acceptance criteria met. |
| "Should work now" | Run the verification. Confidence is not evidence. |
| "Most criteria are met" | All acceptance criteria must be verified. |
| "Guardrail checks are overkill" | High-risk domains require explicit safety verification. |
| "Verification file missing is okay" | Required verification is mandatory for ship. |
| "The code exists so it works" | Existence (Level 1) is not integration (Level 3). Verify all three levels. |
| "Stubs will be filled in later" | Stubs are incomplete code. Incomplete code blocks verification. |

## Hard Gate Enforcement
DO NOT advance past goal verification until the user has explicitly confirmed the verification summary. Passing all three verification levels is necessary but not sufficient — the user must approve before calling `slipway next`.

**Anti-pattern**: "All criteria verified at all three levels, advancing automatically." — Verification checks existence, substance, and wiring, but cannot assess whether the user's actual intent was met. Only the user can confirm that.

## Failure Handling
- Stale or missing verification: keep ship gate blocked until refreshed.
- If verification fails, fix root cause and re-verify (do not patch verification).

